President Donald J. Trump spoke with Prime Minister Paolo Gentiloni of Italy to discuss strengthening bilateral cooperation, particularly in the areas of security and counterterrorism. They discussed issues such as Libya, the influx of migrants and refugees into Europe, and Italy's priorities. President Trump reiterated the U.S. commitment to NATO and emphasized the importance of all NATO allies sharing the financial burden of defense spending. The leaders also agreed to continue working together to eliminate ISIS and other terrorist organizations. President Trump confirmed his attendance at the G-7 Summit in Italy in May and expressed his anticipation to meet with Prime Minister Gentiloni at that time.